The Errors Quoted Include Counting Statistics,
Uncertainties in Counter Efficiencies, Chemical Yield
Determinations, and Summing Corrections. The
Uncertainties of the Radiation Abundances and the
Monitor Cross Sections are not Reflected Therein.

Irradiations were Performed in the Circulating
Beams. The Lengths of Irradiations Ranged from Several
Minutes to Two Hours.
Corrections For Secondary Particles.
Standard Target Assemblies Consisted of a 25 Mum
( OR 50 MUM) Thick Target Foil Sandwiched Between Two
Stacks of Three 25 Mum Aluminium Foils.
For Vanadium, Silver and Indium Targets, Three Target
Foils were Used, Only the Middle One Being Used For
Chemical Processing and the Other Two Serving As Guard
Foils.

- By Authors - Early G-Ray Measurements on Pb and U
Targets  at  1,  2,  and  3  GeV  were  Made  with Na-I
Detectors and Most of the Later Measurements at  3  GeV
And  Higher  were  Made with Ge-Li Detectors.  Whenever
The Measurements were Repeated  with  Ge-Li  Detectors,
The  Agreement with Earlier Result Using Na-I Detectors
Was Almost  Always  Within  Experimental  Uncertainties
+-15%,  Thus  Lending Confidence to All Earlier Results
Obtained with Na-I Detectors.
